For eg 'Sublime text 2'

I installed it using 

sudo add-apt-repository ppa:webupd8team/sublime-text-2
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install sublime-text

Then i have its .deb package file in /var/cache/apt/archives/ folder.. i can get its backup into a folder say /media/akash/Vanilla/Linux Packages/Xubuntu/sublime-text_build-3065_amd64.deb
I can install it any time by this command

cd /media/akash/Vanilla/Linux Packages/Xubuntu/sublime-text_build-3065_amd64.deb
sudo dpkg -i sublime-text_build-3065_amd64.deb

for which i wont need internet.